KEY LEARNING — ROLE-BASED ACCESS CONTROL (RBAC):

Advantage of assigning roles to GROUPS vs individuals:
✓ Scalability: Add/remove users from group = add/remove permissions
✓ Manageability: One role assignment for multiple people
✓ Audit trail: Easy to track who has what permissions
✓ Consistency: All group members have identical permissions
✓ Security: Principle of least privilege (give minimum necessary access)

REAL IT SCENARIO:

Scenario: New employee joins company
Process:
1. Create user account (Day 8)
2. Assign to department group (Day 8 - Sales, HR, IT, etc)
3. Add to security group based on role (Day 9 - Helpdesk, User Support, etc)
4. Security group automatically grants appropriate Entra role
5. Employee has correct permissions instantly
6. If promoted: Remove from one security group, add to another
7. All permissions update automatically

This is how enterprise IT handles access management!

SECURITY BEST PRACTICES LEARNED:

1. Principle of Least Privilege
   - Give users ONLY permissions they need
   - Don't give everyone admin access
   - Review periodically

2. Group-Based Access
   - Assign roles to groups, not individuals
   - Easier to audit and manage
   - Scalable as company grows

3. Separation of Duties
   - Admins ≠ Helpdesk ≠ Compliance
   - Different people, different permissions
   - Prevents abuse

4. Role Definitions
   - Clear job titles = clear role assignments
   - Global Administrator ≠ User Administrator
   - Prevents privilege escalation

